{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EBofokb3qoYrMfqitXt7pM","type":"tool_result","content":"177-## 4. Log Contents\n178-\n179-**Goal:** Capture all output (LLM conversations, script output, status messages) in a\n180:unified log stream. Real-time streaming for active runs, archived files for completed runs.\n181-\n182-### Unified Log Stream\n183-\n--\n206-### Real-Time Streaming\n207-\n208-For active runs, the daemon pipes container stdout to web clients via Server-Sent Events\n209:(SSE). The run detail page gets a live log viewer. LLM and script output are visible\n210-in real-time, not just status changes.\n211-\n212:CLI: `cloche logs <run-id> --follow` streams the unified log in real-time.\n213-\n214-### Post-Run Archival\n215-\n--\n220-\n221-`cloche logs <run-id>` shows the full unified log.\n222-`cloche logs <run-id> --step <name>` filters to a specific step.\n223:`cloche logs <run-id> --follow` streams in real-time.\n224-\n225----\n226-\n--\n263-\n264-1. **Container Deletion** — standalone, no dependencies on other features.\n265-2. **Indicator Lights** — standalone domain logic, needed by Dashboard.\n266:3. **Log Contents** — standalone, changes agent + daemon. Needed by Dashboard for log viewer.\n267-4. **Web Dashboard** — depends on Indicator Lights and Log Contents for full functionality.\n268-5. **Orchestrator** — depends on a working task tracker. Largest feature. Can be developed in parallel with 1-3. Includes the merge queue subsystem."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4342ccdd-9137-491c-9e5c-6183f7ddbbdd","uuid":"93035580-92e0-4d7f-a323-62c30289609d","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"177-## 4. Log Contents\n178-\n179-**Goal:** Capture all output (LLM conversations, script output, status messages) in a\n180:unified log stream. Real-time streaming for active runs, archived files for completed runs.\n181-\n182-### Unified Log Stream\n183-\n--\n206-### Real-Time Streaming\n207-\n208-For active runs, the daemon pipes container stdout to web clients via Server-Sent Events\n209:(SSE). The run detail page gets a live log viewer. LLM and script output are visible\n210-in real-time, not just status changes.\n211-\n212:CLI: `cloche logs <run-id> --follow` streams the unified log in real-time.\n213-\n214-### Post-Run Archival\n215-\n--\n220-\n221-`cloche logs <run-id>` shows the full unified log.\n222-`cloche logs <run-id> --step <name>` filters to a specific step.\n223:`cloche logs <run-id> --follow` streams in real-time.\n224-\n225----\n226-\n--\n263-\n264-1. **Container Deletion** — standalone, no dependencies on other features.\n265-2. **Indicator Lights** — standalone domain logic, needed by Dashboard.\n266:3. **Log Contents** — standalone, changes agent + daemon. Needed by Dashboard for log viewer.\n267-4. **Web Dashboard** — depends on Indicator Lights and Log Contents for full functionality.\n268-5. **Orchestrator** — depends on a working task tracker. Largest feature. Can be developed in parallel with 1-3. Includes the merge queue subsystem.","numLines":33}}
