{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0119vd3NZxzsYQ32DDwi7V3n","type":"tool_result","content":"53-| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n54-| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n55:| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n56-| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n57-\n--\n209-Rules:\n210-- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n211:- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n212-- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n213-- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n214-- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n215-\n216:## Prompt Assembly\n217-\n218:When an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n219-\n220-1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n221-2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n222:3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n223-4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n224-\n225:The assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n226-\n227-## Agent Command Resolution\n--\n311-|----------|-------------|\n312-| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n313:| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n314-| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n315-\n--\n423-Lists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n424-\n425:### `cloche logs`\n426-\n427-```\n428:cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n429-```\n430-\n431-| Flag | Description |\n432-|------|-------------|\n433:| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n434:| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n435:| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n436-\n437:For active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n438-\n439-### `cloche poll`\n--\n492-│       ├── prompt.txt        # User prompt\n493-│       ├── output/\n494:│       │   ├── full.log      # Unified log\n495:│       │   ├── test.log      # Per-step script output\n496:│       │   └── llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n497-│       ├── attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n498:│       └── history.log       # Step execution log\n499-├── src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n500-└── .git/\n--\n509-| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n510-| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n511:| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n512-| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n513-| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n514:| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n515-| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n516-| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4342ccdd-9137-491c-9e5c-6183f7ddbbdd","uuid":"222c0a54-e06c-4df8-9d8d-1d186ee39c8f","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"53-| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n54-| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n55:| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n56-| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n57-\n--\n209-Rules:\n210-- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n211:- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n212-- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n213-- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n214-- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n215-\n216:## Prompt Assembly\n217-\n218:When an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n219-\n220-1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n221-2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n222:3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n223-4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n224-\n225:The assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n226-\n227-## Agent Command Resolution\n--\n311-|----------|-------------|\n312-| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this work